        <div aria-hidden="true" aria-labelledby="label" class="modal" id="about_modal" role="dialog" tabindex="-1">
            <div class="modal-dialog">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h4 class="modal-title" id="label">About SparkWay Maps</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <h5>SparkWay Maps is a route planning service for drivers of electric vehicles.</h5>
                        <p>When you input a range, origin, and destination, SparkWay Maps will give you a route between your origin and destination that routes you through public charging stations to make sure your vehicle always stays charged.</p>
                        <p>You can provide either your type of electric vehicle (if it&#8217;s on our list) or your own estimated range. This lets you adjust exactly how far you're willing to go between charging stops. SparkWay Maps will also warn you if the route it gives you involves going more than 85% of the range you gave between charges, which is especially useful if you're using the manufacturer-given range &mdash; those estimates are sometimes optimistic.</p>
                        <p>Not every electric car can use the same types of chargers. In the <a data-target="#charger-options" data-toggle="modal">Charger Type Options</a> menu, you can select just the types of chargers that work for your car. If you don't know which charger types your car can use, you can check our lists of cars that can use the <a data-target="#dcfast_modal" data-toggle="modal">DC Fast</a> and <a data-target="#j1772_modal" data-toggle="modal">J1772</a> charger types.</p>
                        <p>Once you get a route, you can click on the points SparkWay has routed you through to see more information about the charging station. You can also hover over the little orange marker for any other station to see its name and address.</p>
                        <p><strong>For more information, contact us at <a href="mailto:sparkwaymaps@gmail.com">sparkwaymaps@gmail.com</a>!</strong></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal">OK</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div aria-hidden="true" aria-labelledby="label" class="modal" id="charger-options" role="dialog" tabindex="-1">
