        <div aria-hidden="true" aria-labelledby="label" class="modal" id="dcfast_modal" role="dialog" tabindex="-1">
            <div class="modal-dialog">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h4 class="modal-title" id="label">DC Fast Chargers</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <p>DC Fast chargers use direct current to charge your battery very quickly, usually providing 80&#37; to 100&#37; of a full charge in about 30 minutes.</p>
                        <p><strong>Cars that can use DC Fast chargers include:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Chevrolet Spark EV</li>
                            <li>Commuter Cars Tango T600</li>
                            <li>Mitsubishi 'i'</li>
                            <li>Nissan LEAF</li>
                            <li>Tesla Model S</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal">OK</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div aria-hidden="true" aria-labelledby="label" class="modal" id="j1772_modal" role="dialog" tabindex="-1">
            <div class="modal-dialog">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h4 class="modal-title" id="label">J1772 Chargers</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <p>J1772 chargers are a standard connector type that many electric cars can use. Because J1772 chargers can run at different levels of current and voltage, charge times vary widely. "Level 1" J1772 chargers run at 120V (household voltage in the US) and about 16A, and can fully charge your car overnight. "Level 2" J1772 chargers run at 240V and up to 60A, and can fully charge most cars in about 4 hours.</p>
                        <p><strong>All the vehicles in our dropdown menu can use J1772 charging stations. The Tesla Model S and Tesla Roadster require adaptors to connect to J1772 ports.</strong></p>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal">OK</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
